<%args>

</%args>

<div class="modal fade" id="manage_catalog_usage_info_dialog" name="manage_catalog_usage_info_dialog" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="manageCatalogUsageInfoDialog">
    <div class="modal-dialog modal-lg " role="document">
        <div class="modal-content">
            <div class="modal-header" style="text-align: center">
                <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close"><span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span></button>
                <h4 class="modal-title" id="manageCatalogUsageInfoDialog">How to Add and Manage Catalog</h4>
            </div>
            <div class="modal-body">
                <div class="container-fluid">
                    <p> Only users with vendor role can see and use Manage Catalog section.</p>
                    <hr class ="solid">
                    <h4>
                        How to Add Catalog Items:
                    </h4>
                    <p>You can choose one of the three methods for adding catalog item(s) based on the number of items and details.
                    <li><b>Add Single Item</b>: If you would like to add only one item to the catalog, you can use <b>"Add Single Item"</b> dialog</li>
                    <li><b>Add Multiple Items using List</b>: If you would like to add many items with the same stock type and the same catalog info, using <b>"Add Multiple Items Using List"</b> dialog is the most convenient method.</li>
                    <li><b>Upload Multiple Items</b>: For adding many items with different stock types and each item may have different catalog info, you can use <b>"Upload Multiple Items"</b> dialog.</li>
                    <br>
                    <hr class ="solid">
                    <h4>
                        Important Notes:
                    </h4>
                    <li>Item Name: Currently catalog items include only accesssion, seedlot, population, vector_construct stock type. If you would like to add more stock types, please contact us.</li>
                    <li>Category: This field can be customized. Currently there are four categories for catalog items (released variety, pathogen assay, control, transgenic line), please contact us if you would like to add more categories.</li>
                    <li>When you add new items, 'Item Type', 'Material Type', 'Species' and 'Variety' fields will be filled automatically based on item stock type and associated info stored in the database.</li>
                    <br>
                    <hr class ="solid">
                    <h4>
                        Availability of Catalog Items:
                    </h4>
                    <p>Each item in the catalog has 'available' staus by default. Vendors can change the status to 'unavailable' by using editing catalog info feature on the Catalog Item Detail page. Once the item becomes unavailable, the request/shopping cart link is hidden and users are not able to order the item. </p>
                    <br>
                </div>
                <div class="modal-footer">
                    <button id="close_target_numbers_dialog" type="button" class="btn btn-default" data-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<style>

hr.solid { border-top: 3px solid #bbb; }

</style>

<script>

jQuery(document).ready(function(){

    jQuery('#manage_catalog_usage_info_button').click(function(){
        jQuery('#manage_catalog_usage_info_dialog').modal("show");
    });

});

</script>
